# Local dev and `npm run test:integration` (apply migrations: `npx prisma migrate deploy`)
#
# Prisma expects a full PostgreSQL URL. This line has no credentials (loopback URL only).
# If your Postgres requires a user/password, set the full URL in your real `.env` (gitignored) — never commit it.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://127.0.0.1:5432/bizcode_dev?schema=public

# Required for `npx prisma db seed`: strong secret, local machine only (minimum 8 characters; see `prisma/seed.ts`).
BIZCODE_SEED_SUPERADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Optional: after SuperAdmin seed, upsert a minimal rubro (codigo=1) for local/demo parity (see docs/en/quality/test-environments-parity.md).
# BIZCODE_SEED_FIXTURE_CATALOG=true

# Optional: `npm run bootstrap:superadmin` — alternative to seed; does not update password if the user already exists (see README).
# BIZCODE_BOOTSTRAP_SUPERADMIN_PASSWORD=
# BIZCODE_BOOTSTRAP_SUPERADMIN_USERNAME=Ayelen

# Optional: legacy DBF tree for `npm run migrate:dbf` / `npx tsx scripts/inspect-dbf.ts` when Programa_Viejo is not under the repo root (absolute or relative to cwd).
# PROGRAMA_VIEJO_ROOT=D:/ruta/Programa_Viejo
